es or postponed until after the lockdown. It is not the government’s pleasure to arrest well-meaning members of the society but we will enforce the law as we try to contain the pandemic. “In the same vein, disinformation seems to have become a secondary threat after #COVID19. I would like to implore our news agencies and media to please fact check every information that is put out to avoid causing confusion and making matters worse than they currently are. “Let us work together as we unite, safely in our homes, against #COVID19,” Ganduje tweeted. Earlier, the State Ministry of Health has confirmed that it recorded six additional new cases of coronavirus bringing the number to 27 in the state. The Ministry in a late Friday night tweet confirmed the new cases on it official twitter handle. The tweet reads, “As at 10:56 pm 17th April 2020, Kano state confirms Six (6) additional cases of #COVID19 totaling to 27 cases, 1 death. “Stay At Home, Stay Safe Nigeria and lockdown Kano,” the tweet however reads. vanguard The Kano State Police Command has urged residents in the state to adhere strictly to the lockdown order to contain the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic. Mr. Habu Sani, the state Commissioner of Police, made the call in a statement by the Command’s Spokesman, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, on Friday in… April 17, 2020 In "News" By Abdulmumin Murtala - Kano The Kano State Governor Abdullahi Ganduje has extended the shutdown of civil service activities in the state by two weeks. Ganduje issued instruction of an additional two weeks to stay at home for the civil servants on Monday while receiving a report of the COVID-19… April 6, 2020 In "News" By Abdulmumin Murtala, Kano Kano state governor Abdullahi Ganduje has has lucked down Kano for seven days beginning from 10 pm on Thursday 16 March, 2020. The governor made the announcement after a meeting with various stakeholders in the state and the state security council on Tuesday. ALSO READ: Police uncover… April 14, 2020 In "Co